### Flow of AP webpage sensor data displaying 

1. USER OPENS BROWSER
2. Browser requests: http://192.168.4.1/
3. ESP32 calls index_handler()
4. index_handler() sends STATIC HTML with embedded JavaScript
   (This HTML has placeholders like `<div id='temp'>--</div>`)
5. Browser receives and displays the HTML page
   AT THIS POINT, THE ESP32 IS DONE WITH index_handler() 
6. Browser's JavaScript STARTS RUNNING (on the user's device, NOT the ESP32!)

7. JavaScript says: "Every 300ms, make a NEW HTTP request to /sensor_data"
   
8. Browser requests: http://192.168.4.1/sensor_data
   
9. ESP32 calls sensor_data_handler()
   
10. sensor_data_handler() reads current sensor values from queue/mutex
    
11. sensor_data_handler() creates JSON string like:
    {"temperature": 23.5, "pressure": 1013.2, ...}
    
12. ESP32 sends JSON back to browser
    
13. JavaScript receives JSON and updates the HTML elements:
    document.getElementById('temp').innerHTML = "23.5 Â°C"
    
14. User sees updated numbers (WITHOUT page reload!)
    
15. Wait 300ms, go back to step 7 and repeat forever